ch Associate   at the <A HREF="http://www.dis.uniroma1.it">Dipartimento di   Informatica e Sistemistica</A> (DIS) of the University of Rome "La   Sapienza". I am a member of the DIS <A HREF="../../index.html">Robotics   Laboratory</A>.</BLOCKQUOTE><P><HR><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="#0000AF"><B>Research interests</B></FONT></P><BLOCKQUOTE>My research interests are in the fields of modeling and   control of robotic systems, underactuated manipulators, fault   detection and isolation for nonlinear systems.</BLOCKQUOTE><P><HR><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="#0000AF"><B>Publications</B></FONT></P><P><B>International Journals</B></P><UL>   <LI>A. De Luca, R. Mattone, and G. Oriolo "Control of Redundant   Robots under End-Effector Commands: A Case Study in Underactuated   Robotic Systems," J. of Applied Mathematics and Computer Science,   Vol. 7, No.&nbsp;2, pp.&nbsp;225-251, 1997.</LI>      <LI>A. De Luca, R. Mattone, and G. Oriolo, "Steering a class of   redundant robots through end-effector generalized forces,'' IEEE   Trans. on Robotics and Automation, Vol. 14, No. 2, pp. 329-335,   1998.</LI>      <LI>R. Mattone, G. Campagiorni, F. Galati, "Sorting of items on a   moving conveyor belt. Part 1: A technique for detecting and   classifying objects," Robotics and Computer-Integrated   Manufacturing, Vol.&nbsp;16, pp.&nbsp;76-80, 2000.</LI>      <LI>R. Mattone, M. Divona, and A. Wolf, "Sorting of items on a   moving conveyor belt. Part 2: Performance evaluation and   optimization of pick-and-place operations," Robotics and   Computer-Integrated Manufacturing, Vol.&nbsp;16, pp.&nbsp;81-90,   2000.</LI>      <LI>A. De Luca, R. Mattone and G. Oriolo, "Stabilization of an   underactuated planar 2R manipulator," Int. J. of Robust and   Nonlinear Control, Vol.&nbsp;10, No.&nbsp;4, pp.&nbsp;181-198,   2000.</LI>      <LI>A. De Luca, S. Iannitti, R. Mattone, and G. Oriolo,   "Underactuated manipulators: Control properties and techniques,"   M